<L>__{interior worthington house, dining room night}
<A>__{olive and homer sit at the dining room table, the remnants of an apple pie in front of them. homer is still eating. pictures of wally are on the wall.}
<C>__{olive}
<D>__{i used to hate it when wally went back to college even when it was just college! and this was when his father was still alive... i hated it even then. naturally i hate this more.}
<A>__{homer nods in sympathy. his mouth is stuffed with apple pie.}
<C>__{olive}
<D>__{what i mean is... i would like it very much if you thought you could be happy here, homer.}
<C>__{homer}
<P>__{(wiping his mouth)}
<D>__{mrs. worthington, i feel i'm very lucky to be here.}
<C>__{olive}
<D>__{there's not a lot of work in the winter, and you'll have to tolerate vernon even wally despises him, and wally likes everyone.}
<A>__{olive's thoughts drift; her eyes look up at a photo of wally.}
<C>__{homer}
<D>__{i think wally will be fine, mrs. worthington he seems indestructible to me.}
<C>__{olive}
<P>__{(distracted)}
<D>__{i don't know.}
<P>__{(intently at homer)}
<D>__{just promise me one thing.}
